You understand that?

792
01:01:29,667 --> 01:01:31,259
Very well, sir.

793
01:01:31,336 --> 01:01:32,268
I'll try.

794
01:01:32,337 --> 01:01:33,827
[Knock On Door]

795
01:01:33,905 --> 01:01:34,837
Come in.

796
01:01:34,906 --> 01:01:36,339
Sir,
a destroyer

797
01:01:36,407 --> 01:01:38,102
is coming
alongside.

798
01:01:38,176 --> 01:01:39,108
All right.

799
01:01:39,177 --> 01:01:41,771
We'll go on
with this later.

800
01:01:41,846 --> 01:01:43,370
Yes, sir.

801
01:01:49,687 --> 01:01:51,120
Is that all, sir?

802
01:01:51,189 --> 01:01:52,622
That's all.

803
01:04:50,077 --> 01:04:51,669
[Brakes Squeal]

804
01:04:51,746 --> 01:04:54,271
[Alarm Sounds]

805
01:05:03,424 --> 01:05:04,789
<i>Now hear this.</i>

806
01:05:04,859 --> 01:05:07,794
<i>The smoking lamp is out</i>
<i>throughout the ship.</i>

807
01:05:07,862 --> 01:05:10,797
<i>The smoking lamp is out</i>
<i>throughout the ship.</i>

808
01:05:10,865 --> 01:05:12,799
Hey, Paducah,
the smoking lamp.

809
01:05:12,867 --> 01:05:17,634
I heard it. I heard it.
Do you think I'm deaf?

810
01:05:17,705 --> 01:05:19,969
[Chattanooga Choo-Choo <i>Plays]</i>

811
01:05:35,723 --> 01:05:38,658
Is that the best
you can do?

812
01:05:38,726 --> 01:05:41,354
Yeah. That's
the best I can do.

813
01:05:41,429 --> 01:05:42,657
I'm no hero.

814
01:05:42,730 --> 01:05:45,494
I haven't got any citation
from the admiral.

815
01:05:45,566 --> 01:05:47,796
I haven't
shot down any Zero.

816
01:05:47,868 --> 01:05:49,802
Look here, Scott.
I'm sorry.

817
01:05:49,870 --> 01:05:51,303
Well, then, shut up.

818
01:05:51,372 --> 01:05:53,169
Wait a minute, you two.

819
01:05:53,240 --> 01:05:55,504
Take it easy.
What is this?

820
01:05:55,576 --> 01:05:58,170
Sorry. I guess
we're all a little jumpy.

821
01:05:58,245 --> 01:05:59,678
Relax. As for you, Scott,

822
01:05:59,747 --> 01:06:02,682
there are no stars here.
This isn't Hollywood.

823
01:06:02,750 --> 01:06:05,617
When it's time for you
to take your bows,

824
01:06:05,686 --> 01:06:07,620
we'll turn
on the spotlights.

825
01:06:07,688 --> 01:06:10,623
Now you're just a part
of a team,

826
01:06:10,691 --> 01:06:13,626
and you'll play as
the team plays. Understood?

827
01:06:13,694 --> 01:06:14,718
Yes, sir.

828
01:06:20,774 --> 01:06:23,208
[Chattanooga Choo-Choo
<i>Plays Loudly]</i>

829
01:08:19,493 --> 01:08:21,620
[Blows Whistle]

830
01:08:23,764 --> 01:08:25,197
Now hear this.

831
01:08:25,265 --> 01:08:26,698
Now hear this.

832
01:08:26,767 --> 01:08:30,203
The captain will address
the personnel of the ship.

833
01:08:33,774 --> 01:08:35,708
Men, ever since
Pearl Harbor,

834
01:08:35,776 --> 01:08:37,710
our country
has been asking,

835
01:08:37,778 --> 01:08:41,839
''Where is our navy?
Why don't they fight?''

836
01:08:41,915 --> 01:08:43,542
<i>Because of our</i>
<i>unorthodox maneuvers,</i>

837
01:08:43,617 --> 01:08:46,211
<i>I know you've been</i>
<i>asking the same question.</i>

838
01:08:46,286 --> 01:08:48,345
<i>I must confess,</i>
<i>so have I.</i>

839
01:08:48,422 --> 01:08:51,550
<i>We've suffered many</i>
<i>casualties, dead and wounded.</i>

840
01:08:51,625 --> 01:08:53,616
<i>We've been humiliated.</i>

841
01:08:53,694 --> 01:08:56,891
<i>We've had to avoid combat</i>
<i>and run away from the enemy</i>

842
01:08:56,964 --> 01:08:59,057
<i>when we've been aching</i>
<i>to knock them</i>

843
01:08:59,132 --> 01:09:00,497
<i>clean out of the sky.</i>

844
01:09:00,567 --> 01:09:03,559
<i>We asked ourselves why</i>
<i>we're not permitted to fight,</i>

845
01:09:03,637 --> 01:09:06,003
<i>why we could not</i>
<i>avenge our dead,</i>

846
01:09:06,073 --> 01:09:07,506
<i>strike back in our defense.</i>

847
01:09:07,574 --> 01:09:08,905
<i>Five minutes ago,</i>

848
01:09:08,976 --> 01:09:12,104
<i>I received a message which</i>
<i>answers all our questions.</i>

849
01:09:12,179 --> 01:09:13,612
<i>After Pearl Harbor,</i>

850
01:09:13,680 --> 01:09:16,581
<i>our country was faced</i>
<i>with its greatest disaster.</i>

851
01:09:16,650 --> 01:09:18,174
<i>The situation</i>
<i>was desperate,</i>

852
01:09:18,252 --> 01:09:21,415
<i>and only a desperate and</i>
<i>brilliant strategy could save us.</i>

853
01:09:21,488 --> 01:09:24,013
<i>Our navy pinned its hope</i>
<i>on one thing</i>--

854
01:09:24,091 --> 01:09:26,821
<i>theJapanese inability</i>
<i>to deviate from a plan</i>

855
01:09:26,894 --> 01:09:28,327
<i>once it had been made.</i>

856
01:09:28,395 --> 01:09:32,024
<i>We knew their next move was</i>
<i>to capture Pearl Harbor,</i>

857
01:09:32,099 --> 01:09:34,033
<i>but first they'd</i>
<i>have to take Midway.</i>

858
01:09:34,101 --> 01:09:35,432
<i>We deceived theJaps</i>

859
01:09:35,502 --> 01:09:38,130
<i>by making them think we'd</i>
<i>scattered over the ocean,</i>

860
01:09:38,205 --> 01:09:40,537
<i>that Midway</i>
<i>would be a pushover.</i>

861
01:09:40,607 --> 01:09:43,041
<i>In the meanwhile,</i>
<i>we secretly concentrated</i>

862
01:09:43,110 --> 01:09:45,510
<i>our entire naval strength</i>
<i>at Midway.</i>

863
01:09:45,579 --> 01:09:47,012
<i>That was our trap.</i>

864
01:09:47,080 --> 01:09:50,049
<i>You men, this carrier,</i>
<i>and her escort</i>

865
01:09:50,117 --> 01:09:52,051
<i>were the bait</i>
<i>to that trap.</i>

866
01:09:52,119 --> 01:09:53,552
<i>It was a nasty job.</i>

867
01:09:53,620 --> 01:09:57,056
<i>It has cost us heavily</i>
<i>in men and equipment.</i>

868
01:09:57,124 --> 01:10:00,059
TheJaps thought they saw
four of our carriers

869
01:10:00,127 --> 01:10:01,560
at widely separated places.

870
01:10:01,628 --> 01:10:04,563
They only saw one.
That was us.

871
01:10:04,631 --> 01:10:07,065
Three times Tokyo
reported us sunk.

872
01:10:07,134 --> 01:10:10,535
Twice, we nearly were,
but we're still afloat.

873
01:10:10,604 --> 01:10:13,232
<i>I'm happy to tell you</i>
<i>the strategy has worked.</i>

874
01:10:13,307 --> 01:10:15,104
<i>The trap has been sprung.</i>

875
01:10:15,175 --> 01:10:16,574
<i>Believing us scattered</i>
<i>over the ocean,</i>

876
01:10:16,643 --> 01:10:19,373
<i>the mainJap fleet</i>
<i>is headed for Midway.</i>

877
01:10:19,446 --> 01:10:22,506
<i>They're going in</i>
<i>for the kill. So are we.</i>

878
01:10:22,583 --> 01:10:24,016
<i>We're through</i>
<i>running away.</i>

879
01:10:24,084 --> 01:10:25,517
<i>We're through</i>
<i>pulling punches.</i>

880
01:10:25,586 --> 01:10:27,019
<i>Our mission</i>
<i>is accomplished,</i>

881
01:10:27,087 --> 01:10:30,022
<i>and from here on in,</i>
<i>we fight.</i>

882
01:10:30,090 --> 01:10:32,320
- Yay!
- Yay!

883
01:11:41,161 --> 01:11:44,494
TheJap fleet is headed for Midway
in three columns.

884
01:11:44,564 --> 01:11:47,089
One is here
with the carrier <i>Soyu.</i>

885
01:11:47,167 --> 01:11:49,601
One is here
with the carrier <i>Kaga.</i>

886
01:11:49,670 --> 01:11:51,399
One is with the carrier <i>Hiru.</i>

887
01:11:51,471 --> 01:11:54,599
Now, their rear is protected
by a formation

888
01:11:54,675 --> 01:11:57,701
headed by the cruisers
<i>Mikuma</i> and <i>Mogami.</i>

889
01:11:57,778 --> 01:12:00,212
Our heavy ships
are hopelessly outnumbered.

890
01:12:00,280 --> 01:12:02,441
TheJap fleet
mustn't be allowed

891
01:12:02,516 --> 01:12:04,381
to get
within range of them.

892
01:12:04,451 --> 01:12:07,545
The battle of Midway
must be won in the air

893
01:12:07,621 --> 01:12:11,057
by this carrier's planes,
two that will join us,

894
01:12:11,124 --> 01:12:12,591
and the fortresses
on Midway.

895
01:12:14,127 --> 01:12:17,563
When theJaps find out
what they've run into,

896
01:12:17,631 --> 01:12:19,895
they're going
to come after you

897
01:12:19,966 --> 01:12:21,399
with everything they've got,

898
01:12:21,468 --> 01:12:24,869
but this is the battle
we've been praying for.

899
01:12:26,306 --> 01:12:29,241
We've got it--
on our own grounds,

900
01:12:29,309 --> 01:12:31,038
on our own terms.

901
01:12:32,412 --> 01:12:33,379
Good luck.

902
01:13:10,917 --> 01:13:12,680
<i>Pilots...</i>

903
01:13:12,753 --> 01:13:14,812
<i>stand by</i>
<i>to start engines.</i>

904
01:13:14,888 --> 01:13:16,549
<i>Stand clear propellers.</i>

905
01:13:18,458 --> 01:13:19,550
<i>Start engines.</i>

906
01:13:47,154 --> 01:13:49,019
B.G., all set?

907
01:13:50,657 --> 01:13:51,681
Ready, sir.

908
01:13:51,758 --> 01:13:54,852
O'Neal, got your
recognition code straight?

909
01:13:54,928 --> 01:13:57,089
Yes, sir.
One for this morning

910
01:13:57,164 --> 01:13:58,597
and one
for this afternoon.

911
01:14:02,769 --> 01:14:04,100
We'll celebrate tonight

912
01:14:04,171 --> 01:14:06,196
with a nice,
fresh vegetable salad.

913
01:14:06,273 --> 01:14:08,332
The first
from my seagoing farm.

914
01:15:27,621 --> 01:15:29,054
Sir, last enemy position,

915
01:15:29,122 --> 01:15:33,058
bearing 2-1 -5 true,
1 50 miles.

916
01:16:14,100 --> 01:16:16,330
Molton to Squadron,
there's our target.

917
01:16:31,117 --> 01:16:32,550
Molton to Squadron,

918
01:16:32,619 --> 01:16:35,554
remember, when you think
you're in close,

919
01:16:35,622 --> 01:16:38,420
go in closer
before you drop that fish.

920
01:19:07,073 --> 01:19:10,008
Molton to Squadron,
join up.

921
01:19:10,110 --> 01:19:11,509
<i>Come on,join up.</i>

922
01:19:11,578 --> 01:19:13,011
<i>Jacobson, rendezvous,</i>
<i>join up.</i>

923
01:19:13,079 --> 01:19:15,206
<i>I can't.</i>
<i>There's a Zero on your tail.</i>

924
01:19:15,281 --> 01:19:17,715
<i>There's one on yours, too.</i>
<i>Join up.</i>

925
01:19:17,784 --> 01:19:18,716
<i>You all right, Hale?</i>

926
01:19:18,785 --> 01:19:19,717
<i>Yeah, Mr. Molton.</i>

927
01:19:19,786 --> 01:19:22,220
Relay this
throughout the ship.

928
01:19:22,288 --> 01:19:23,277
Radio Room?

929
01:19:23,356 --> 01:19:26,018
Relay these messages
throughout the ship.

930
01:19:26,092 --> 01:19:27,719
<i>Wassum's out</i>
<i>like a flower.</i>

931
01:19:27,794 --> 01:19:29,159
<i>Stand by for anything.</i>

932
01:19:29,229 --> 01:19:31,789
<i>There ought to be fighters.</i>

933
01:19:31,865 --> 01:19:33,230
<i>Watch that Zero</i>
<i>up there.</i>

934
01:19:33,299 --> 01:19:35,824
<i>He won't budge.</i>
<i>He's an old-timer.</i>

935
01:19:35,902 --> 01:19:37,733
<i>What's that Zero</i>
<i>doing, Hank?</i>

936
01:19:37,804 --> 01:19:39,738
<i>He ain't saying.</i>
<i>Just hanging there.</i>

937
01:19:39,806 --> 01:19:41,239
<i>They'll</i>
<i>make a pass soon.</i>

938
01:19:41,307 --> 01:19:42,740
<i>They tagging</i>
<i>our outfit?</i>

939
01:19:42,809 --> 01:19:44,140
<i>Are you kidding?</i>

940
01:19:44,210 --> 01:19:47,236
<i>Shut up. Never mind</i>
<i>the crystal ball gazing.</i>

941
01:19:49,382 --> 01:19:50,314
<i>Come on,you</i>--

942
01:19:50,383 --> 01:19:51,315
<i>Shut up!</i>

943
01:19:52,852 --> 01:19:55,753
<i>1 2 o'clock! Something coming</i>
<i>through the formation.</i>

944
01:19:55,822 --> 01:19:57,255
<i>Wait till they come in.</i>

945
01:19:57,323 --> 01:19:58,756
<i>Where's our fighters?</i>

946
01:19:58,825 --> 01:20:00,258
<i>Watch the ponies</i>
<i>up there.</i>

947
01:20:00,326 --> 01:20:01,258
<i>All right,</i>
<i>all right.</i>

948
01:20:01,327 --> 01:20:02,419
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

949
01:20:02,495 --> 01:20:04,759
<i>Criminy! There's</i>
<i>another batch coming!</i>

950
01:20:04,831 --> 01:20:06,765
<i>All right,</i>
<i>I've got him!</i>

951
01:20:06,833 --> 01:20:08,494
<i>You take him,Joe!</i>

952
01:20:08,568 --> 01:20:10,763
<i>Two more at 2 o'clock</i>
<i>over your right wing.</i>

953
01:20:10,837 --> 01:20:11,769
<i>Get him!</i>

954
01:20:11,838 --> 01:20:13,271
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

955
01:20:13,339 --> 01:20:14,271
<i>Got him.</i>

956
01:20:14,340 --> 01:20:15,272
<i>Shut up.</i>

957
01:20:16,976 --> 01:20:18,773
<i>Everybody all right?</i>
<i>Pilot to</i>--

958
01:20:18,845 --> 01:20:19,777
<i>1 1 o'clock!</i>

959
01:20:19,846 --> 01:20:20,778
<i>Cri-ola.</i>

960
01:20:20,847 --> 01:20:21,779
<i>Ya-hoo!</i>

961
01:20:21,848 --> 01:20:23,281
<i>Shut up, will you</i>--

962
01:20:23,349 --> 01:20:24,281
<i>1 1 o'clock!</i>

963
01:20:24,350 --> 01:20:25,783
<i>They're</i>
<i>rolling under.</i>

964
01:20:25,852 --> 01:20:27,285
<i>I got it.</i>

965
01:20:27,353 --> 01:20:29,287
<i>Key-ristmas!</i>
<i>How many are there?</i>

966
01:20:29,355 --> 01:20:30,788
<i>Smack 'em down!</i>

967
01:20:30,857 --> 01:20:32,222
<i>Let 'em</i>
<i>come around!</i>

968
01:20:32,292 --> 01:20:33,782
<i>All right, all right.</i>

969
01:20:33,860 --> 01:20:35,293
<i>Swing us around.</i>

970
01:20:35,361 --> 01:20:37,295
<i>Got him! Got him!</i>

971
01:20:37,363 --> 01:20:38,796
<i>1 1 o'clock!</i>

972
01:20:38,865 --> 01:20:40,230
<i>Ed! Ed!</i>

973
01:20:40,300 --> 01:20:41,790
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

974
01:20:41,868 --> 01:20:43,301
<i>They got Ed.</i>

975
01:20:43,369 --> 01:20:44,802
<i>No, I'm all right.</i>

976
01:20:44,871 --> 01:20:46,463
<i>Ed, is that you?</i>

977
01:20:46,539 --> 01:20:47,471
<i>Yeah.</i>

978
01:20:47,540 --> 01:20:49,303
<i>They got Hank.</i>

979
01:20:49,375 --> 01:20:51,309
<i>Gosh, there they go.</i>

980
01:20:51,377 --> 01:20:53,811
<i>There's one chute.</i>
<i>Two to go.</i>

981
01:20:53,880 --> 01:20:55,313
<i>He's rolling over.</i>

982
01:20:55,381 --> 01:20:57,611
<i>Come on, guys.</i>
<i>Get out of there.</i>

983
01:20:57,684 --> 01:20:59,117
<i>Bail out of there.</i>

984
01:20:59,185 --> 01:21:00,812
<i>Why don't they</i>
<i>get out?</i>

985
01:21:00,887 --> 01:21:02,320
<i>Jeepers,</i>
<i>he's really spinning.</i>

986
01:21:02,388 --> 01:21:05,323
<i>Come on,you guys.</i>
<i>Get out. Get out!</i>

987
01:21:05,391 --> 01:21:06,756
<i>There's one more out</i>--

988
01:21:06,826 --> 01:21:08,760
<i>2 o'clock!</i>
<i>They're coming in!</i>

989
01:21:08,828 --> 01:21:10,762
<i>They're coming</i>
<i>under you, Ben.</i>

990
01:21:10,830 --> 01:21:12,764
<i>Hold your hats.</i>
<i>I'm coming.</i>

991
01:21:12,832 --> 01:21:14,766
<i>Take 'em, Bill,</i>
<i>take 'em!</i>

992
01:21:14,834 --> 01:21:15,766
<i>Look out!</i>
<i>5 o'clock!</i>

993
01:21:15,835 --> 01:21:17,598
<i>I'm coming up from 5!</i>

994
01:21:17,670 --> 01:21:18,762
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

995
01:21:18,838 --> 01:21:20,772
<i>How's our sweetheart,</i>
<i>Mr. Holloway?</i>

996
01:21:20,840 --> 01:21:23,274
<i>Spurting oil</i>
<i>like her heart's busted.</i>

997
01:21:23,343 --> 01:21:24,742
<i>Close the intercom.</i>

998
01:21:24,811 --> 01:21:26,278
<i>Watch out.</i>
<i>Zero on your tail.</i>

999
01:21:26,346 --> 01:21:27,574
<i>Blue plate special</i>
<i>coming up.</i>

1000
01:21:27,647 --> 01:21:29,274
<i>Get him! Get him!</i>

1001
01:21:29,349 --> 01:21:30,782
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

1002
01:21:30,850 --> 01:21:32,283
<i>Sink,you</i>--

1003
01:21:32,352 --> 01:21:33,444
<i>[Explosion]</i>

1004
01:21:33,519 --> 01:21:34,952
<i>Goodbye, him.</i>

1005
01:21:35,021 --> 01:21:37,012
<i>Nice work.</i>
<i>Square in the belly.</i>

1006
01:21:37,123 --> 01:21:38,524
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

1007
01:21:39,425 --> 01:21:42,360
<i>Pilot to Radioman,</i>
<i>are you all right?</i>

1008
01:21:42,428 --> 01:21:43,861
<i>Mike, are you</i>
<i>all right?</i>

1009
01:21:43,929 --> 01:21:46,864
<i>I think that burst got him,</i>
<i>Mr.Jacobson.</i>

1010
01:21:46,932 --> 01:21:48,194
<i>Better bail out,</i>
<i>Tommy.</i>

1011
01:21:48,267 --> 01:21:49,256
<i>We haven't much time.</i>

1012
01:21:49,335 --> 01:21:50,859
<i>Were you hit, Mike?</i>

1013
01:21:50,936 --> 01:21:52,369
<i>Shut off your intercom,</i>
<i>Jacobson.</i>

1014
01:21:52,438 --> 01:21:54,872
<i>I can't.</i>
<i>My equipment's shot up.</i>

1015
01:21:54,940 --> 01:21:56,373
<i>Mike, are you O.K.?</i>

1016
01:21:56,442 --> 01:21:57,875
<i>It's my leg, sir.</i>

1017
01:21:57,943 --> 01:21:59,376
<i>Can you move them?</i>

1018
01:21:59,445 --> 01:22:01,879
<i>Mike, can you</i>
<i>move your legs?</i>

1019
01:22:04,450 --> 01:22:05,382
<i>Uh-uh.</i>

1020
01:22:05,451 --> 01:22:06,816
<i>We're burning</i>
<i>back here.</i>

1021
01:22:06,886 --> 01:22:08,820
<i>You'd better</i>
<i>bail out, sir.</i>

1022
01:22:08,888 --> 01:22:11,322
<i>I haven't got</i>
<i>the altitude, Mike.</i>

1023
01:22:11,390 --> 01:22:12,823
<i>We'll take this ride</i>
<i>together.</i>

1024
01:22:12,892 --> 01:22:15,827
<i>Jacobson,join up.</i>
<i>Do you hear me, Hans?</i>

1025
01:22:15,895 --> 01:22:17,829
<i>Join up, I tell you.</i>

1026
01:22:27,907 --> 01:22:29,340
<i>Enemy planes approaching.</i>

1027
01:22:29,408 --> 01:22:30,841
<i>All hands stand by.</i>

1028
01:22:30,910 --> 01:22:32,571
<i>Enemy planes approaching.</i>

1029
01:22:37,249 --> 01:22:39,080
Hard left!
Hard left!

1030
01:23:17,156 --> 01:23:18,817
Hard right rudder!

1031
01:23:18,891 --> 01:23:22,349
[Bomb Whistling]

1032
01:23:30,836 --> 01:23:32,827
The bomb that hit aft

1033
01:23:32,905 --> 01:23:34,338
damaged
the hydraulic lines

1034
01:23:34,406 --> 01:23:36,340
that control
the landing gear.

1035
01:23:44,717 --> 01:23:46,048
How long to repair?

1036
01:23:46,118 --> 01:23:47,085
Hard to say, sir.

1037
01:23:47,153 --> 01:23:49,519
The returning planes
will be low on gas.

1038
01:23:49,588 --> 01:23:52,785
I want that gear operating
by the time they're in sight.

1039
01:23:52,858 --> 01:23:54,849
I want a report
on damage

1040
01:23:54,927 --> 01:23:56,360
and our maximum
possible speed.

1041
01:24:14,313 --> 01:24:17,646
The engine room reports
we can only make 20 knots.

1042
01:24:17,716 --> 01:24:20,583
We'll need 25 knots
to land our planes.

1043
01:24:20,653 --> 01:24:21,813
Report that
below.

1044
01:24:21,887 --> 01:24:22,911
Aye, aye, sir.

1045
01:24:34,900 --> 01:24:37,835
Call out the after-damage
control party.

1046
01:24:37,903 --> 01:24:40,337
20 men from the V-3 division.

1047
01:24:40,406 --> 01:24:41,839
Clear that damage.

1048
01:24:46,912 --> 01:24:48,072
Hurry it up!

1049
01:25:27,186 --> 01:25:28,813
The flight deck officer reports

1050
01:25:28,888 --> 01:25:31,823
it's impossible to repair
the after-flight deck

1051
01:25:31,891 --> 01:25:33,688
in less than 45 minutes.

1052
01:25:35,895 --> 01:25:39,331
You got just 20 minutes
to repair that flight deck.

1053
01:25:39,398 --> 01:25:40,330
When the planes return,

1054
01:25:40,399 --> 01:25:42,424
they'll have a deck
to land on.

1055
01:25:42,501 --> 01:25:45,561
Sir, escort has picked up
enemy submarine

1056
01:25:45,638 --> 01:25:47,071
on the sound
detector.

1057
01:25:48,140 --> 01:25:50,335
We got a plane left
to launch?

1058
01:25:50,409 --> 01:25:51,341
One, sir.
Just repaired.

1059
01:25:51,410 --> 01:25:52,342
Launch her.

1060
01:25:53,846 --> 01:25:55,837
Launch catapult bomber.

1061
01:25:55,915 --> 01:25:57,473
Launch catapult bomber.

1062
01:25:57,583 --> 01:25:58,845
<i>Launch catapult bomber.</i>

1063
01:25:58,918 --> 01:26:00,852
<i>Launch catapult bomber.</i>

1064
01:26:02,488 --> 01:26:04,353
Rapid gunners,
hold your fire.

1065
01:26:04,423 --> 01:26:05,913
Catapult plane
being launched.

1066
01:26:27,379 --> 01:26:29,313
We're going
to be hit.

1067
01:26:54,406 --> 01:26:56,840
Who was flying
that plane?

1068
01:26:56,909 --> 01:26:58,843
Ensign Cunningham, sir.

1069
01:26:58,911 --> 01:27:01,846
That the one
they call Cookie?

1070
01:27:01,914 --> 01:27:03,848
Yes, sir.

1071
01:27:03,916 --> 01:27:07,079
Sir, Torpedo Five
and fighter escort returning.

1072
01:27:19,365 --> 01:27:21,299
Prepare to land planes.

1073
01:27:21,367 --> 01:27:23,858
Prepare to land planes.

1074
01:27:24,937 --> 01:27:26,802
Code this
to the other carriers--

1075
01:27:26,872 --> 01:27:29,306
As soon as
planes have landed,

1076
01:27:29,375 --> 01:27:31,309
changing course
60 degrees southeast

1077
01:27:31,377 --> 01:27:32,810
for cover of rain squall

1078
01:27:32,878 --> 01:27:34,311
till repairs are completed.

1079
01:27:34,380 --> 01:27:35,813
Aye, aye, sir.

1080
01:28:00,372 --> 01:28:02,602
[Playing Reveille]

1081
01:28:02,674 --> 01:28:05,666
Red, this is Molton.
What now?

1082
01:28:05,744 --> 01:28:08,611
Radar picked up disturbances
at 85 miles,

1083
01:28:08,680 --> 01:28:10,113
altitude 5,000 feet,

1084
01:28:10,182 --> 01:28:12,616
but they've settled down
to a single object.

1085
01:28:12,684 --> 01:28:15,812
We can hear it now.
Sounds like a TBF.

1086
01:28:15,888 --> 01:28:17,116
You hear that, Molton?

1087
01:28:17,189 --> 01:28:18,281
Could be a TBF.

1088
01:28:18,357 --> 01:28:19,790
Any of yours
straggling?

1089
01:28:19,858 --> 01:28:21,189
Wait a minute.

1090
01:28:24,696 --> 01:28:27,631
Oscar was just passing
over the cargo

1091
01:28:27,699 --> 01:28:29,132
when she blew up.

1092
01:28:29,201 --> 01:28:31,135
Maybe...

1093
01:28:32,237 --> 01:28:35,138
Scott is the only one
not accounted for.

1094
01:28:35,207 --> 01:28:36,139
Thanks, Red.

1095
01:29:10,142 --> 01:29:11,473
Mr. Scott?

1096
01:29:12,744 --> 01:29:15,713
You figure the carrier
ducked under that soup?

1097
01:29:20,185 --> 01:29:21,618
Maybe.

1098
01:29:21,687 --> 01:29:23,621
They weren't
at the rendezvous.

1099
01:29:23,689 --> 01:29:25,554
Keep your chin up.

1100
01:29:25,624 --> 01:29:29,116
I'm not afraid of anything anymore,
Mr. Scott.

1101
01:29:29,194 --> 01:29:31,059
Today's my birthday.

1102
01:29:31,130 --> 01:29:34,122
How old are you
today, B.G.?

1103
01:29:34,199 --> 01:29:35,962
1 7, sir.

1104
01:29:46,345 --> 01:29:47,607
You hear that Benny?

1105
01:29:47,679 --> 01:29:49,146
Hey, Benny.

1106
01:30:14,239 --> 01:30:16,173
I'll get him down.

1107
01:31:04,289 --> 01:31:07,156
Mr. Scott,
couldn't we break radio silence

1108
01:31:07,226 --> 01:31:08,955
long enough
to get a fix?

1109
01:31:14,733 --> 01:31:18,169
Nobody would like that
better than I would, B.G.

1110
01:31:18,237 --> 01:31:19,363
No dice.

1111
01:31:21,240 --> 01:31:24,175
Brother, how I could use
a spotlight now.

1112
01:31:40,259 --> 01:31:41,886
That's Ensign Scott, sir.

1113
01:31:45,764 --> 01:31:48,028
He doesn't know
our new course.

1114
01:31:53,272 --> 01:31:55,206
Couldn't we break
radio silence?

1115
01:31:55,274 --> 01:31:59,370
You don't have to give him
a position theJaps can check.

1116
01:31:59,444 --> 01:32:01,878
Just say,
''We're right under you.

1117
01:32:01,947 --> 01:32:04,711
Ceiling, 50 feet.
Come on down.''

1118
01:32:04,783 --> 01:32:09,152
If you think theJaps
have a radar fix on him,

1119
01:32:09,221 --> 01:32:11,746
let me go up.
I can lead him down.

1120
01:32:11,823 --> 01:32:15,657
That's as useful to the enemy
as breaking radio silence.

1121
01:32:15,727 --> 01:32:17,524
We can't risk
this carrier.

1122
01:32:17,596 --> 01:32:19,154
What about that kid--

1123
01:32:19,231 --> 01:32:20,198
That's enough, Molton.

1124
01:32:20,265 --> 01:32:21,664
Check
your casualty list

1125
01:32:21,733 --> 01:32:23,667
and reform
your squadron.

1126
01:32:23,735 --> 01:32:25,168
Yes, sir.

1127
01:32:28,006 --> 01:32:30,167
[Engine Faltering]

1128
01:32:37,249 --> 01:32:42,186
[Plane Diving]

1129
01:32:42,254 --> 01:32:43,687
[Crash]

1130
01:33:04,576 --> 01:33:07,136
First it was Gus,

1131
01:33:07,212 --> 01:33:09,146
then Brainard,

1132
01:33:09,214 --> 01:33:11,011
then Chuck,

1133
01:33:11,083 --> 01:33:13,142
and then Hans.

1134
01:33:13,218 --> 01:33:16,153
But at least he had
a fighting chance.

1135
01:33:16,221 --> 01:33:19,156
But not Oscar.
He didn't have a chance.

1136
01:33:19,224 --> 01:33:21,658
Up there,
going back and forth,

1137
01:33:21,727 --> 01:33:24,127
and nobody made an effort
to help him down.

1138
01:33:43,749 --> 01:33:46,684
Do you know
what these are?

1139
01:33:48,253 --> 01:33:49,948
They're casualty lists.

1140
01:33:51,757 --> 01:33:55,454
They're obituaries of
a long list of friends of mine.

1141
01:33:55,527 --> 01:33:58,690
Yes, friends.

1142
01:33:59,765 --> 01:34:02,700
If I seemed too tough
on the boys,

1143
01:34:02,768 --> 01:34:05,202
it was because I was
responsible for them.

1144
01:34:05,270 --> 01:34:07,135
I didn't want to lose them

1145
01:34:07,205 --> 01:34:10,641
any more than I wanted to
lose those boys up there.

1146
01:34:10,709 --> 01:34:13,143
You think I wanted
to let Scott fly

1147
01:34:13,211 --> 01:34:15,145
until he dove
into the sea?

1148
01:34:15,213 --> 01:34:18,649
You think I want to dream
about them on a raft

1149
01:34:18,717 --> 01:34:20,150
until their bodies rot?

1150
01:34:20,218 --> 01:34:22,152
I'm an air officer.

1151
01:34:22,220 --> 01:34:26,657
There are things I can do
and things I can't do.

1152
01:34:26,725 --> 01:34:28,659
I can check casualty lists,

1153
01:34:28,727 --> 01:34:31,662
and I can order more men
into the air

1154
01:34:31,730 --> 01:34:33,163
to become new casualties.

1155
01:34:33,231 --> 01:34:36,667
I can refuse to endanger
the lives of 3,000 men

1156
01:34:36,735 --> 01:34:39,670
in order to save the lives
of three men.

1157
01:34:39,738 --> 01:34:42,172
I do those things
because they're my job,

1158
01:34:42,240 --> 01:34:44,174
and I've got to do them.

1159
01:34:44,242 --> 01:34:45,675
But to be accused

1160
01:34:45,744 --> 01:34:47,678
of refusing
to save those men

1161
01:34:47,746 --> 01:34:49,714
because I didn't
want to save them--

1162
01:34:49,781 --> 01:34:52,181
[Ringing]

1163
01:34:55,754 --> 01:34:57,688
Torpedo Ready Room.
Molton speaking.

1164
01:34:58,757 --> 01:35:00,190
It's for you, sir.

1165
01:35:04,262 --> 01:35:05,194
Yes.

1166
01:35:12,204 --> 01:35:13,136
Very good.

1167
01:35:18,710 --> 01:35:21,543
A destroyer picked up
Scott and his crew.

1168
01:35:21,613 --> 01:35:24,377
His radioman was lost,

1169
01:35:24,449 --> 01:35:28,146
but he and his gunner
are O.K.

1170
01:35:28,220 --> 01:35:30,654
They got him!
He's back in!

1171
01:35:30,722 --> 01:35:34,158
How about that?
He's back in the ballgame.

1172
01:35:50,242 --> 01:35:51,300
Thanks, Ed.

1173
01:35:54,145 --> 01:35:55,077
Period.

1174
01:35:56,648 --> 01:35:57,580
Secure.

1175
01:36:01,753 --> 01:36:03,277
How about that?

1176
01:36:42,227 --> 01:36:44,161
Commander Harper.

1177
01:36:44,229 --> 01:36:47,164
Orders for tomorrow--

1178
01:36:47,232 --> 01:36:49,166
1 4 TBFs,

1179
01:36:49,234 --> 01:36:51,668
1 9 SB2Cs...

